name: MeterBar
classdesc:
JET meter bar

A meter bar is typically used to display or accept user feedback on a product or service. 
<oj-c-meter-bar value='4'></oj-c-meter-bar>

Accessibility

The application is strongly encouraged, even though it is not required, to populate the aria-label attribute on the element with meaningful descriptors as the oj-c-meter-bar element does not provide a default descriptor.

If an application is using thresholds, reference lines or custom baseline, they need to include the information for screender readers using the following methods:

  • aria-describedby
  • aria-labelledby
  • aria-label
  • datatip

If you are using indicatorColor, applications are responsible for making sure that the color meets the minimum contrast ratio.

Keyboard

Key Action
Enter Submit the current value of the meter bar.
Tab Move focus to next element and submit the current value of the meter bar.
Shift + Tab Move focus to previous element.
End Increase the meter bar's transient value to max value. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.
Home Decrease the meter bar's transient value to zero. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.
UpArrow Increase the meter bar's transient value. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.
DownArrow Decrease the meter bar's transient value. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.
LeftArrow Decrease the meter bar's transient value in left-to-right locales. Increase the meter bar's transient value in right-to-left locales. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.
RightArrow Increase the meter bar's transient value in left-to-right locales. Decrease the meter bar's transient value in right-to-left locales. Value is set after using Enter or Tab to submit.

Touch End User Information

Gesture Action
Drag Value change when readonly is false.

name: max
description: Integer value specifying the maximum value of the meter bar.

name: min
description: Integer value specifying the minimum value of the meter bar.

name: readonly
description: Defines whether the value of the meter bar can be changed by the end user.

name: value
description: The value of the meter bar.

name: baseline
description:
Define the baseline value of the bar. If undefined, defaults to minimum value of the meter bar.
The baseline value must be between the min and max.

name: step
description: Specifies the increment by which values can be changed by the end user when readonly is false. The step must be a positive value that is smaller than the difference between the min and max.

name: color
description: Specifies the color of the meter bar indicator. Only applies when thresholdDisplay is not set to indicator.

name: indicatorSize
description: Specifies the ratio of relative thickness of the indicator to the plot area.

name: plotArea
description: Specifies the plot area of the meter bar.

name: orientation
description: Specifies the orientation of the meter bar to render.

name: referenceLines
description: Specifies the array of objects defining the reference lines for the meter bar.

name: thresholdDisplay
description: Controls whether the current threshold is displayed on the indicator, in the plot area, or if all the thresholds are displayed in the plot area.

name: thresholds
description: An array of objects defining the thresholds for the meter bar.

name: describedBy
description:
Used to establish a relationship between this component and another element.
A common use is to tie a label, which can be a text in a div or some other HTML element, and the oj-c-meter-bar together for accessibility.
The oj-label element has a label-id, which is used by the described-by attribute to tie the two components together to facilitate correct screen reader behavior.

name: labelledBy
description:
Used to establish a relationship between this component and another element.
A common use is to tie a label, which can be a text in a div or some other HTML element, and the oj-c-meter-bar together for accessibility.
The oj-label element has a label-id, which is used by the labelled-by attribute to tie the two components together to facilitate correct screen reader behavior.

name: size
description: Specifies the size of the meter bar.

ojvalues.name: fit
ojvalues.description: Meter Bar that fits the available space

name: datatip
description:
The function that returns a custom datatip string for given value of meter bar. The function is called with DatatipContext as context. If datatip is undefined,
meter bar will use the default datatip. If the returned value of the function is null, no datatip is shown.

name: transientValue
description: A read-only property for retrieving the transient value from the meter bar. It is triggered when dragging over the meter bar.

name: setProperty
description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

name: getProperty
description: Retrieves the value of a property or a subproperty.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

name: setProperties
description: Performs a batch set of properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.
